                    <h2>The Great Coffee Farms</h2>
                    <p>The coffee plantations were founded on large monocultural properties worked by slaves, later replaced by salaried workers: the large coffee farms.</p>
                    <p>These farms became famous for their typical architecture and equipment. Tanks in which the grain is washed soon after harvest, terraces for drying, selection and processing machines are part of this environment. The slave Slave Senzala or free-working colonies finalize the characterization of coffee farms. The coffee farm, from the seed to the cup, was a small world, almost isolated.</p>
